@andrecayton21 You misinterpreted what I meant about Julio. It’s Julio, anyone should be excited to have him, it’s just we didn’t throw to him, so his production was not anywhere near what fans were hoping for. Julio still had some amazing catches as a Titan, he was just under utilized and we lost our star WR for a pick that turned into Burks the following year. Treylon isn’t bad, per say, he just has a problem being healthy and he was not ready to be WR1 in the NFL. I don’t expect anything to come out of the D Hop visit, while it would be nice to get him, our starting QB is almost out the door for the league, and our backup hasn’t played a professional snap yet, so too early to make a call on his transition into the league. Levis could be another Zach Wilson, or he could actually be something. Malik’s arm just isn’t there, despite some of the nice throws he had last year, it’s just not at the NFL caliber yet. I would very much like to see the Titans get it together, but with their new field being turf, and our training staff, I find it best to have zero expectations of the season going either way.
